def correct_bracketing(brackets: str):
    """ brackets is a string of "(" and ")".
    return True if every opening bracket has a corresponding closing bracket.

    >>> correct_bracketing("(")
    False
    >>> correct_bracketing("()")
    True
    >>> correct_bracketing("(()())")
    True
    >>> correct_bracketing(")(()")
    False
    """
    if len(brackets) == 0:
        return True
    if brackets[0]!= "(":
        return False
    if brackets[-1]!= ")":
        return False
    return all(bracket == ")" for bracket in brackets[1:-1])
